so that FDA reviewer can use the same open source package. And also at that time for the advanced

00:36:43.800 --> 00:36:49.800
methodology, we built an internal preparatory R package to wrap up the method. And then we want

00:36:49.800 --> 00:36:56.600
to submit that package to FDA. And as you may know that for all the submission to FDA, you need to go

00:36:56.600 --> 00:37:01.479
through the electronic gateway and how to submit the package through the electronic gateway.

00:37:02.520 --> 00:37:09.320
So eventually we made it, we made a submission, but with a lot of question marks and we were not

00:37:09.320 --> 00:37:14.520
quite sure that whether we follow the best practice for those submissions. So I remember

00:37:14.520 --> 00:37:20.919
that in 2021, our team presented at the R pharma conference at Harvard at that time, it was an

00:37:20.919 --> 00:37:26.439
in-person conference. And it was very interesting that we actually met many people from different

00:37:26.439 --> 00:37:32.280
companies having similar experiences. People all started to use R for regulatory submission

00:37:32.280 --> 00:37:38.679
or clinical trial reporting. And they realized that there are certain industry standard or

