languages. So in 2022, a number of cross-industry collaborations has been established with the

00:37:54.760 --> 00:37:59.800
passionate people from different companies and with a very strong engagement from FDA.

00:38:00.439 --> 00:38:04.840
I'm calling out two efforts here because those are the ones I'm most familiar with.

00:38:05.479 --> 00:38:10.679
One is the R consortium, R submission working group, which is a collaboration with FDA

00:38:10.679 --> 00:38:18.919
to showcase public available open pilots and to show how to submit using R and what are some

00:38:18.919 --> 00:38:25.159
good practices and also try to identify gaps for R-based or open source language-based submission

00:38:25.159 --> 00:38:31.639
to FDA. And the other one is called Pharmaverse. And as you heard from earlier presentations that

00:38:31.639 --> 00:38:37.560
Pharmaverse is an open source collaboration effort trying to develop high quality technical

00:38:37.560 --> 00:38:45.000
solutions to bridge any gaps in a clinical trial reporting space. So in 2022, it was really

00:38:45.000 --> 00:38:50.760
exciting that we finished the pilot one from R consortium working group. We were able to

00:38:51.719 --> 00:38:58.840
showcase how to use R for RBA submission and then engage with FDA review or to identify gaps,

